Wash and dry all produce. Halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise), then cut crosswise
into thin half-moons. Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince until you have 1 TBSP.
Quarter @lime{2 %quartered}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(sliced, separating
whites from greens).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine ginger, scallion whites, @ground pork{20%ounce}, 
@panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, and 2 TBSP @bulgogi sauce{8%ounce} (save the rest 
for later). Season with @salt{1%tsp} and @pepper{}. Shape into 1-inch balls.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add zucchini and season with salt
and pepper. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat;
transfer to another medium bowl.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan. Add @shredded carrots{8%ounce}; season
with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add to bowl
with zucchini, then toss with half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} (save the rest
for later). Set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and
cook, turning, until browned all over, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add remaining bulgogi sauce to pan with meatballs. Bring to a simmer, then cover
pan and reduce heat to mediumlow.

> TIP: If your pan doesn't have a lid, cover with aluminum foil.

Steam until meatballs are cooked through, about ~{5%minutes}. Turn off heat.
Meanwhile, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{17%ounce} in its packet to break
up, then microwave according to package instructions.

Place rice in a #large bowl{} and toss with remaining sesame oil and the juice
from 1 lime wedge. Divide between plates and top with veggies and meatballs.
Drizzle with remaining sauce from pan and @sriracha{2%teaspoon} (to taste; skip 
this for the kids). Garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and scallion greens.
Serve with remaining lime wedges.